"As the Islamic Republic of Iran has repeatedly announced, Iran-Russia nuclear cooperation is for peaceful purposes" and Iran carries out its peaceful atomic programs under the supervision of the International Atomic Energy Agency.
--Russia reiterated that its cooperation with Iran in the nuclear industry fully conforms to all international commitments of Moscow and Tehran, including those on the nonproliferation of nuclear weapons.
--Iran has rejected as "unfounded" an allegation by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu that Iran is seeking access to atomic warheads.
